## 🧠 CONTEXT & GROUND RULES

You are implementing a set of production features for **VetTrack**, a veterinary equipment tracking PWA.
Before writing a single line of code, read and internalize the following rules. They are non-negotiable.

### Tech Stack (do not deviate)

|Layer          |Technology                                                                                            |
|---------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Frontend       |React 18 + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS                                                           |
|UI Components  |**Shadcn UI** (existing components only, do not add new registry items unless instructed)             |
|Icons          |**Lucide React** (never substitute with other icon sets)                                              |
|Animation      |**Framer Motion**                                                                                     |
|Backend        |Node.js + **Express** via `tsx`                                                                       |
|ORM            |**Drizzle ORM** — schema lives in `server/db.ts`                                                      |
|Database       |**PostgreSQL**                                                                                        |
|Background Jobs|**BullMQ** + **Redis** — workers live in `server/workers/`, schedulers boot from `start-schedulers.ts`|
|Offline-First  |**Dexie.js** (v3.2.7) + **TanStack Query** with Optimistic UI                                         |
|API Client     |`src/lib/api.ts` — all server calls go through here                                                   |
|Auth           |**Clerk**                                                                                             |
|Multi-tenancy  |Every DB table has a `clinicId` column — every query MUST filter by it                                |

### Coding Style Rules

1. **Database First** — every feature starts with a Schema change in `server/db.ts`. Run `npx drizzle-kit generate` and `npx drizzle-kit push` after schema changes.
1. **Never use `python3`** — validate TypeScript with `npx tsc --noEmit` after every file change.
1. **Hebrew only in JSX text/UI labels** — all identifiers, variables, function names, types, and file names must be in English.
1. **Complete files only** — never output partial diffs. Always provide the full corrected file content.
1. **No unrelated refactoring** — touch only what is needed for the feature being implemented.
1. **Minimal fix philosophy** — the smallest change that correctly solves the problem.
1. **Every new API endpoint** must be registered in `src/lib/api.ts` and typed in `src/types/`.
1. **Every new BullMQ worker** must be imported and initialized in `start-schedulers.ts`.
1. **Every Dexie table addition** must be versioned with a migration block.

