## FEATURE 3 — Charge & Power Tracking

### Goal

Track whether returned equipment is plugged in. Alert staff if a device is not plugged in within a configurable time window.

### Schema (server/db.ts)

Add to the `equipment_returns` (or equivalent checkout/return) table:

```typescript
isPluggedIn: boolean('is_plugged_in').default(false),
plugInDeadlineMinutes: integer('plug_in_deadline_minutes').default(30),
plugInAlertSentAt: timestamp('plug_in_alert_sent_at'),
```

Run `npx drizzle-kit generate` then `npx drizzle-kit push`.

### Worker (server/workers/chargeAlertWorker.ts)

Create a BullMQ **delayed job** (not repeatable):

- Queue name: `"charge-alert"`
- Triggered immediately on a Return event where `isPluggedIn = false`
- Delayed by `plugInDeadlineMinutes` minutes using BullMQ’s `delay` option:
  
  ```typescript
  await chargeAlertQueue.add('check-plug', { returnId, equipmentId, clinicId }, {
    delay: plugInDeadlineMinutes * 60 * 1000,
    jobId: `plug-check-${returnId}`, // idempotent
  });
  ```
- Job processor logic:
1. Re-fetch the return record by `returnId`
1. If `isPluggedIn` is now `true` — do nothing (user plugged it in)
1. If still `false` — send push notification to clinic staff:
  - Title: `"🔋 ציוד לא מחובר לחשמל"`
  - Body: `"${equipment.name} לא חובר לחשמל תוך ${plugInDeadlineMinutes} דקות`
1. Set `plugInAlertSentAt = NOW()`

When a return is **updated** and `isPluggedIn` changes to `true`, remove the pending job:

```typescript
await chargeAlertQueue.remove(`plug-check-${returnId}`);
```

Register worker in `start-schedulers.ts`.

### API

- `POST /api/returns` — extend to accept `isPluggedIn: boolean` and `plugInDeadlineMinutes?: number`
- `PATCH /api/returns/:id` — accept `isPluggedIn: boolean`; if `true`, cancel the BullMQ job

### Frontend

- In the return/check-in form, add a toggle (`Switch` from Shadcn) labeled `"חובר לחשמל?"`
- Default value: `false`
- If `false`, show a subtle warning: `"התראה תישלח לאחר X דקות אם לא יחובר"`
- In the equipment detail view, show a power status badge:
  - Plugged: `Plug` icon (Lucide), green
  - Not plugged: `BatteryWarning` icon (Lucide), orange/red

### Tests (Feature 3)

Create `server/tests/chargeAlertWorker.test.ts`:

```typescript
// ✅ Delayed BullMQ job is enqueued when return is created with isPluggedIn = false
// ✅ Job is NOT enqueued when return is created with isPluggedIn = true
// ✅ Job uses jobId 'plug-check-{returnId}' (idempotency — no duplicates)
// ✅ Job processor: does nothing if isPluggedIn is true when job fires
// ✅ Job processor: sends push notification if isPluggedIn is still false when job fires
// ✅ Job processor: sets plugInAlertSentAt = NOW() after sending notification
// ✅ PATCH /api/returns/:id with isPluggedIn=true removes the pending BullMQ job
```

Create `server/tests/returnsApi.test.ts`:

```typescript
// ✅ POST /api/returns accepts isPluggedIn boolean field
// ✅ POST /api/returns accepts optional plugInDeadlineMinutes (defaults to 30)
// ✅ PATCH /api/returns/:id rejects requests from a different clinic
// ✅ Unauthenticated POST /api/returns returns 401
```

Create `src/tests/ChargeToggle.test.tsx`:

```typescript
// ✅ Switch defaults to false (not plugged in)
// ✅ Warning text is visible when isPluggedIn = false
// ✅ Warning text is hidden when isPluggedIn = true
// ✅ Correct Lucide icon displayed per plug state
```

